answerText: Diels-Alder[10] The substituents in the Diels-Alder reaction's transition state often adopt this conformation, in which the electron-withdrawing groups on the dienophile are pointing towards and are underneath the diene.

question: Question: This reaction takes a diene and a dienophile and combines them to form a cyclohexene derivative. [10] Name this pericyclic reaction named for a pair of German chemists.
